content.description: Start low on a sloping rail and crank your way through sloping crimps on the good rock
content.location: From the skyline look uphill and to the east for a large snag. This problem is in the snag area. Hike up and left past Jabroni brothers to a small open bench, then hike back left towards the snag

content.description: Sit start on jugs. Climb up the huge juggy side-pull feature. Landing is not the best.

Start on the Obvious double underclings, climb up through crimps, pinches, and jugs to a committing finish through slopey edges and an easy mantle. Classic! You can also start on the detatched block if desired and climb straight up - a touch easier.

Start on a good left hand crimp and a poor right hand sloper crimp. Climb up the overhang via sloping pockets and crimps and a big move to the lip! Watch out for the dead tree on top that has been manually bucked!!!
content.location: Hike up the trail to a clump of large fir trees where you will find a few low-ball warm up problems and a cool looking cave. Manual Buck is a minute walk uphill and to the left from the cave, but is hard to see from afar. 5-10 minutes from the base, depending on the route you take.

content.description: Sit start on good compression slopers, trend up and left via small crimps - eventually finishing on good slopers and a savior jug.
content.location: 500 yards up the hill from Skyline boulder

content.description: Start on a positive rail and utilize a good pocket like hold to a mellow top out.
content.location: Left of Jabroni brothers, 50 feet uphill from Skyline boulder

content.description: Sit Start matched on a small crimp rail in a low angle scoop like dihedral feature. Climb out the buldge via a nice crack feature to a somewhat desperate top out.
content.location: From Skyline boulder, walk up the hill approximately 50 feet.

content.description: Probably the most accessible and best problem in this small corridor. Sit start on good holds - utilize positive edges to an easy top out.
content.location: Far right side of the cooridoor.

content.description: Stand start on an incut crimp rail - use interesting footwork to make a long reach to another incut edge - mellows out up top. Great rock - good landing - enjoy!
content.location: This boulder is in a small cooridor directly above the Skyline boulder

content.description: Stand start on good incut holds, climb straight up utilizing a sharp crimp.
content.location: Left most problem on the Fast Lane boulder.

content.description: Nice concentration of boulder problems up on the south face of Mt. Elden. Standout problems include Skyline arête and Manual Buck. There is certainly potential for more problems up here! To best find this area hike around on the base and look for an obvious clump of fir trees.
